<p>I'm using WinForm. I have a textbox and a button. </p>  <p>Goal: The button should validate if the textbox is a currency format. If the textbox is a currency format, a message should display currency format. If not then a message should display Error wrong format. </p>  <p>Example of currency format: </p>  <p>$1,234.00</p>  <p>$12,345.00</p>  <p>$123,000.00</p>  <p>$1.00</p>  <p>Update:</p>  <p>This is what i had, but this is wrong.</p>  <pre><code>    Private void button3_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)     {             currencyTextbox = Convert.ToString(textBox4.Text);          string money = currencyTextbox;          string s = currencyTextbox;         float f;         if (float.TryParse(s, NumberStyles.AllowCurrencySymbol              | NumberStyles.AllowDecimalPoint | NumberStyles.AllowThousands,              CultureInfo.GetCultureInfo("en-US"), out f))         {             MessageBox.Show("Ok");         }         else         {             MessageBox.Show("Wrong");         }      } </code></pre>  <p>Test cases: </p>  <p>$12.00 - OK</p>  <p>$12,000 - OK</p>  <p>$12,3,00 - OK - (Invalid)</p>  <p>$12,3,00# - Wrong</p>